      • group

        <R> java.util.Map<R,Queryable<T>> group(Function<? super T,R> func)
        Groups the elements of this Queryable using the given function. Note: This function will usually execute the query by copying the underlying elements into a new collection. A change to the underlying collection will therefore (if not specified otherwise) not be applied to the returned object. See execute().
        Parameters:
        func - The function that returns a value that is used to group the elements of this Queryable.
        Returns:

      • execute

        Queryable<T> execute()
        Performs all previous operations based on the currently present elements and returns the result as an independent instance of Queryable. Future changes to the underlying collection won't be applied to result of this method.
        Returns:
        A independent copy of this Queryable.
